name: Human Movement Laboratory
description: In this course students will be introduced to the study of human movement across a range of topics (e.g., eye-movements, balance, and walking), and will have the opportunity to collect and analyze human movement data. Additional topics include basic aspects of experimental designs, data analysis and interpretation of such data.
prerequisites: [PSYB01H3 or PSYB04H3] and [PSYB07H3 or STAB22H3 or STAB23H3]
